title: Gas-s-s-s (1970)
description:
GAS-S-S-S! or It Became Necessary to Destroy the World in Order to Save It
1970

Directed by Roger Corman
Written by George Armitage

MPEG-4 Nero Digital Cinema AVC
720x384
Audio: AAC-HE

From the MGM Midnite Movies DVD released 2003.

Corman's last "counterculture" film before leaving A.I.P. to form New World Pictures. In this story, a gas has killed off all the adults in the world, leaving the youth to fend for themselves and start a new order.  It ain't easy.  Filmed in the great Southwestern desert/plains of New Mexico, it's an interesting time capsule with a number of young actors & actresses who would become quite famous -- Ben Vereen, Cindy Williams, Talia Shire (Coppola) . . .
